column5: Just had an awesome dinner. Filet O Fish Alaskan style. Halibut burgers are to die for!!!!
Yum!!!!  Looks rather tasty?
that's $10 worth of halibut down here!!!  awesome!
Hey I thought you were on a no carb diet!  Looks awesome though, save me some.
I am Mike, but the diet goes out the window when I'm sick. Back to the diet tomorrow.
looks like whole wheat buns and a nice healthy piece of fish....  nothing remotely unhealthy about that!
Looks yummy!  email some to me please?
You must be sick,theres only two.  Nicely lightly battered. PERFECT.
Looks awsome but I would get rid of the cheese and add a tiny bit of mayo and a splash of lemon....
Now that just looks so tasty!!!   I may have to make some of my own
melt the cheese next time, looks yummy for the tummy
Finger lickin good!!!
melt the cheese next time, looks yummy for the tummy  It was well melted by the time I bit into it. Thought about toasting the bun but it was too much work.
No Tartar ?
Nope, don't like that goo. Did put some malt vinegar on though. I think they would taste good topped with my slaw too.
Fresh halibut is on my bucket list. When I do catch one, I might not be able to resist the urge to take a bite of it while its still moving lol   S.

hahahaha love it Sinker. i can totally imagine you doing that as well.  this thread made me drool.  Today for lunch I had some "fresh" halibut from a "nice" restaurant.  Not so good.  But hey, I tried, lol.

Fresh halibut is on my bucket list. When I do catch one, I might not be able to resist the urge to take a bite of it while its still moving lol  Probably the best fish EVER!!!  Dave, my tuna melts for supper tonight didn't even come close to that scrumptiousness.
Nope, don't like that goo.  This little clip popped to mind
I would take that over any meal I had this week! And we have eaten well.....  I might have to substitute with Pickeral however..  G
